on the translation of machine language programs.wautomatic translation of machine languageprograms is becoming a highly desirable goal with the advent of new large-scale computers.  the pitfalls thatmake it difficult to achieve completely automatic translations are analyzed, and it is shown that these areprimarily of a semantic nature.  a semi-automatic procedure for resolving semantic problems is suggested.cacm december, gaines, r. s.ca jb march ,   : pm